latestPosts.caption:
Pinch me 🥹✨ • I couldn’t be more excited, proud and *SO* grateful to introduce my very own jewellery collection with @mabeanda 😭🐚✨ 

A 9 piece edit of go with every outfit hoops, stacking rings, minimal chains and (of course) pearls, inspired by the jewels you never take off. Those ride or die, wear every single day pieces that transform just jeans & a tee. For me, a flash of warm gold and pearl against the simplest of looks is an instant way to elevate - I’m never not seen in a pair of bright gold hoops ✨

These designs really are straight from my brain/heart, and I cannot wait for you all to pick your favourites 🥹💫 • Launching next week • 19.10.23 •

———

📸 ~ @nicfordphoto ✨

Yesterday’s Monday Mum mode look + hair mask & minimal, under 10 minute make-up 👇🏻
 
• great tee with solid crew-neck (@cosstores 🤌🏻)
• jeans that work from park to pub* (@watthebrand 🤌🏻)
• a throw in the car, carry a kid on your hip, not too hot, looks OK creased, throw over everything jacket (@hm 🤌🏻)
• jewels to pull together/add warmth to a face in desperate need of some tan (@mabeanda | own collection 🤌🏻)
• sunnies to finish/harmonise (gold jewels, gold frames 🤌🏻)
• a pretty much indestructible, fits everything in + looks chic bag* (@marksandspencer @marksandspencerstyle 🤌🏻)

*some pr gifts

Styled my new £18 Sainsbury’s @tuclothing shorts up, what do we think? Come summer I’ll be adding just a vest, havainas & great sunnies to run around in with Rivs too, but as soon as I bought them I knew I’d wear them with everything 🤌🏻 (shout out @goodmannersstyle for looking so epic in hers I went in search for them!) 

I get such a kick out of making something affordable look super chic & expensiveeee via styling so maybe there’s a series in this. Let me know if you’d love to see more of the same ☺️

Aside from an obsession with a great basic vest (can’t stop, won’t stop buying them ✌🏻), my capsule summer edit is pretty sorted. So for a 2025 refresh, I’m looking at a few small (purse-friendly) ways I can reimagine my favourite combinations for this season. I love adding touches of a trend my way, finding a bargain that screams me in a silhouette I know I’ll wear year after year and playing with colour when most of the time I don’t. 

Here are 5 easy ways to add a touch of summer to a wardrobe you already love, never sacrificing your own style but being open to playing a little, and adding in pieces that transform outfits you already swear by 🌞

I LOVED putting this together for the grid - let me know if you’d love more of these! 🫶🏻
